        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 9:01PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 901 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Brevard, or near Rosman, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Toxaway, Graveyard Fields, Horse Shoe, Balsam Grove, Cruso,
Penrose, Connestee, Etowah, Looking Glass, and Forge Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
